pullRequest.body:
Rename `succAbove_below`, `succAbove_above`, `predAbove_below` and `predAbove_Above` to more appropriate things, and vary and extend these results to allow for faster proofs elsewhere.

---
This is part of the ongoing efforts to break up #9145. In particular this is the critical update, where we start seeing benefits in
longer proofs elsewhere (see `succAbove_predAbove` for an example). It's probable that after this update, many of the proofs
in SimplexCategory can be shortened.

Feel free to update `scripts/style-exceptions.txt` to bypass the CI failure on this file. Since you plan to split the file in a follow up PR.
Thanks. I'll look at doing so.

(I don't quite understand the syntax here - also, some other file, Mathlib/RingTheory/DedekindDomain/Ideal.lean, appears to be failing style checks, but I am not sure I modified this one: what gives?)
I am a bit worried that all these `simp` lemmas will fire many TC synths for `NeZero n`. I will call a benchmark on this PR to see if it impacts the library.

This is fair. I would be happy to have the `n + 1` versions as simp lemmas if that would be preferred? I had them in an earlier iteration of this work but I understood that NeZero n was preferred if possible.

In this case, thinking about it the NeZero is only needed to state the lemma (because it is vacuously true for n = 0 because of i). So maybe I can change the statement somewhat? Essentially what I want is the zero on the right, and it's getting access to that notation that's the kicker.
It does seem to impact it. Assuming that's what is causing the issue.
Hmm, weird that only that one file would see such a negative impact. I wonder if it's a fluke? I'll bump master and run another bench.
It's in the approximate topic area, so it might be that whatever that file does it does so in a way that's very sensitive to this change?

> Hmm, weird that only that one file would see such a negative impact. I wonder if it's a fluke? I'll bump master and run another bench.

Well, we've [seen](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/noisy.20.60FilteredColimitCommutesFiniteLimit.60) this [before](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/9655#issuecomment-1887793644).
